subMembers.name: Configuration
subMembers.description: This section describes properties used to configure the UI component.

subMembers.name: isDirty
subMembers.description: Specifies whether the component's current value differs from the initial value.

subMembers.name: isValid
subMembers.description: Specifies or indicates whether the editor's value is valid.

subMembers.name: name
subMembers.description: The value to be assigned to the `name` attribute of the underlying HTML element.

subMembers.name: readOnly
subMembers.description: Specifies whether the editor is read-only.

subMembers.name: validationError
subMembers.description: Information on the broken [validation rule]. Contains the first item from the [validationErrors] array.

subMembers.name: validationErrors
subMembers.description: An array of the [validation rules] that failed.

subMembers.name: validationMessageMode
subMembers.description: Specifies how the message about the [validation rules] that are not satisfied by this editor's value is displayed.

subMembers.name: validationMessagePosition
subMembers.description: Specifies the position of a validation message relative to the component. The validation message describes the [validation rules] that this component's value does not satisfy.

subMembers.name: validationStatus
subMembers.description: Indicates or specifies the current validation status.

Methods.name: clear()
Methods.description: Resets the [value] property to the default value.

Methods.name: reset(value)
Methods.description: Resets the [value] property to the value passed as an argument.

Events.name: onValueChanged
Events.description: A function that is executed after the UI component's [value] is changed.

Events.name: valueChanged
Events.description: Raised after the UI component's [value] is changed.
